<paragraph id="0703185BFF9EFF8ABA0CFBC40BBEFEE5" blockId="21.[827,1443,1769,1883]" lastBlockId="22.[145,760,197,280]" lastPageId="22" lastPageNumber="1363" pageId="21" pageNumber="1362">
<emphasis id="35C8C449FF9EFF89BA0CFBC40DA4F903" box="[827,1266,1769,1791]" italics="true" pageId="21" pageNumber="1362">
Diagnosis: 
<taxonomicName id="C0BC63D8FF9EFF89BAEAFBC70DA4F903" authorityName="SCHMID" authorityYear="1982" box="[989,1266,1769,1790]" class="Insecta" family="Xiphocentronidae" genus="Caenocentron" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Trichoptera" pageId="21" pageNumber="1362" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="ideolus">Caenocentron ideolus</taxonomicName>
</emphasis>
is similar to 
<taxonomicName id="C0BC63D8FF9EFF89BA0CFA260ABCF8E0" baseAuthorityName="MOSELY" baseAuthorityYear="1934" box="[827,1002,1800,1821]" class="Insecta" family="Xiphocentronidae" genus="Caenocentron" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Trichoptera" pageId="21" pageNumber="1362" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="trilineatum">
<emphasis id="35C8C449FF9EFF89BA0CFA260ABCF8E0" box="[827,1002,1800,1821]" italics="true" pageId="21" pageNumber="1362">C. trilineatum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by the narrow apical projection of coxopodite. It can be diagnosed by the presence of an elongate ventral process on the paraproct; coxopodite with the ventral projection of coxopodite short and with shorter setae; harpago with a basal brush of setae; and sternum IX overall deltoid in lateral view.
</paragraph>
